        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 6 at 8:18PM MDT by NWS Rapid City SD</headline>
        <description>At 817 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
northwestern Custer State Park, or near Custer, moving southeast at
10 mph.

HAZARD...Half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Custer, Blue Bell, Center Lake, Stockade Lake, Mount Coolidge, Legion
Lake, Black Hills Playhouse, and Custer State Park.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
